    {
      q: "How does ConvertOcean convert files without uploading them?",
      a: "ConvertOcean uses WebAssembly (WASM) and local JavaScript compilers to convert files directly inside your browser window. When you load a tool page, all required code is loaded into your browser tab cache, allowing your device's CPU/GPU to parse, compile, and format files locally. Since your file data remains inside sandboxed tab memory, it is never transmitted over the internet or uploaded to a remote server."
    },
    {
      q: "Is my confidential business or financial data safe when converting files?",
      a: "Yes, converting sensitive files on ConvertOcean is completely safe. Because all data processing happens locally on your device (client-side), confidential documents, financial statements, internal spreadsheet formulas, and tax details are never uploaded to any remote server or third-party database. You retain full data sovereignty at all times."
